## üí° Clinical Notes & Commentary

### Traditional Understanding
"Qing Shang" means "clear the upper" referring to clearing heat from upper jiao, especially head and face regions. "Fang Feng" means "dispel wind" - addressing wind-heat patterns affecting sense organs. Classic approach for inflammatory conditions of head, face, and upper body with both heat and wind components.

### Modern Pharmacology
Research shows anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant effects. Huang Lian and Huang Qin contain berberine and flavonoids with anti-bacterial properties. Lian Qiao provides anti-viral compounds. Studies demonstrate benefits in acne, conjunctivitis, and upper respiratory infections. The combination helps reduce inflammation and prevent secondary infections.

### Clinical Experience
Excellent for inflammatory conditions affecting head, face, and sense organs. Particularly effective for acne in teenagers and young adults with heat constitution. Often provides rapid improvement in acute infections of eyes, ears, and sinuses. Best results when combined with appropriate topical care and dietary modifications.

### Dosage & Administration
**Standard Dose**: Decoct above doses twice daily, or 6-9g granules twice daily
**Preparation**: Standard decoction, can be used for topical washes (cooled)
**Timing**: Between meals, can increase frequency for acute infections
**Duration**: 1-3 weeks for acute conditions, 6-12 weeks for chronic skin problems

